        <div class="documentation-section">
            <h2>Documentation & Formulas</h2>
            <details>
                <summary>Temperature Conversions</summary>
                <p>Temperature conversions require specific formulas:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Celsius to Fahrenheit:</strong> Â°F = (Â°C Ã— 9/5) + 32</li>
                    <li><strong>Fahrenheit to Celsius:</strong> Â°C = (Â°F - 32) Ã— 5/9</li>
                    <li><strong>Celsius to Kelvin:</strong> K = Â°C + 273.15</li>
                    <li><strong>Kelvin to Celsius:</strong> Â°C = K - 273.15</li>
                    <li><strong>Fahrenheit to Kelvin:</strong> K = (Â°F - 32) Ã— 5/9 + 273.15</li>
                    <li><strong>Kelvin to Fahrenheit:</strong> Â°F = (K - 273.15) Ã— 9/5 + 32</li>
                </ul>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Other Unit Conversions</summary>
                <p>Most other units are converted by multiplying or dividing by a fixed factor relative to a base unit within their category. For example, for Length, 'Meter' is the base.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>To convert from Unit A to Unit B:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Convert value in Unit A to the base unit: `valueInBase = inputValue Ã— factorA_to_Base`</li>
                            <li>Convert valueInBase to Unit B: `result = valueInBase / factorB_to_Base` (or `valueInBase Ã— factorBase_to_B`)</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>The internal system uses factors that convert a unit *to* its category's base unit. So the formula used is: `(inputValue * sourceUnit.factor) / targetUnit.factor`.</li>
                </ul>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
